result.short_description: Q2P: Clean Client existence check at initialization
result.description: Q2P: Clean Client existence check at initializationThis incident has been created automatically. Since the Customer is not involved, the incident has to be solved internally by Service Provider/Support/Development to avoid negative impact for the customer business.Diagnostic Information:Health Check Name: /SMB/CLMS_BC_Q2P_PROCESS_CHECKEvent Name: GENERAL_Q2P_ERRORSEvent Context: E0071BF8D1D91EE9A9D4FD622B294B0EApplication Component: SV-CLD-FRM-INFAdditional Description:Note: This incident will be closed automatically as soon as the action leading to the incident is completed successfully in the system. If the incident is closed manually before this has happened,it will either be reopened automatically or a new incident will be created for this issue.Client: 716 CREATED_AT : 07/15/2019 02:26:15 PERFORMED_ACTION : Q2P: Clean Client existence check at initialization PROJECT_TYPE : Business Change Project TARGET_STATUS : Completed DiagnosisClean Client is not specified for current system.System ResponseIn non-starter systems with new Q2P enabled and no Clean Clientavailable, no transport requests can be created since the transporttarget (Clean Client in Q system) cannot be determined. In a clientwhere transport request creation is required, no Q2P project will becreated. Activation cannot be done, and any update or upgrade will fail.ProcedureMake sure the Clean Client has been set up correctly.In customer-like Cloud systems there should be a separate client(standard is client 050) that is defined as Clean Client in tableCLMS_TENANT. This setting needs to be maintained by Cloud Operations.In non-customer-like systems (e.g. internal test systems, CTC = 0) thereshould be a corresponding entry in the user settings (transaction/SMB/Q2P_UCS_MAINT) which defines one of the available clients as CleanClient. This setting can be changed directly with the transactionmentioned before.Procedure for System AdministrationCheck the system setup and make sure there is a Clean Client availablein this system.
